Post description: Hi, As it's not possible to add additional HTML within <head> on MoodleCloud, I was hoping to be able to use @import in my custom Boost preset SCSS file to embed a Google Font. This works, but it stops the Font Awesome icons from displaying. Here's the relevant section of my SCSS (added as an additional theme preset file): 
```text
@import "fontawesome";


@import "bootstrap";


@import "moodle";


@import url("
https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Raleway:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&display=swap
");
```
 What am I missing? Thanks for your help. Jez
